=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> I was reading Khirsa's (I tihnk) warrior thread in General when some people mentioned that, in my interpretation, a FBSS for a warrior may not be as useful as a belt with AC on it.<br>
<br>
I have a 34 warrior with @720AC using a FBSS currently. Should I forgoe the taunt factor that the FBSS gives me for the AC of a Straw Spun belt? The SSB has ac 10 and is really freaking easy to acquire compared to the other comparable 10AC belts in the game. <br>
<br>
My weapons are low/mid level right now, 2 yaks, icetooth claw, gleaming ss from trak, mith staff, nathsar 2hs...<br>
<br>
With these low/mid range weapons, would I be forsaking my taunting abilities by giving up the FBSS for an AC belt? If I had a CSS and a Lammy or other high damage, low delay weapons, where I could easily taunt mobs off of people w/o the FBSS, the added AC from a SSB would be beneficial. <br>
<br>
I'm a troll at have 1500hp and the aforementioned @720AC; so I can take some hits. But if I can't taunt the mobs of of the other tanks, what good does my AC do me?<br>
<br>
Currently, I have a hard time keeping mobs on me if I am not the puller. My 1hs, 2hs, 2hb, kick, bash are all maxxed; and those are the weapons I normally use. I know I'm not the damage dealer of a monk or rogue... But if I can't keep mobs on me with a FBSS; how effective would I be without the FBSS?<br>
<br>
Anyhoo, just rambling.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/u999ping.showPublicProfile?language=EN>999ping</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 4:39:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> Stick with the sash.<br>
<br>
1. Taunting is your job<br>
2. Item Haste is the most significant way a melee has to boost damage output<br>
3. Warriors can get ac out the wazoo anyway<br>
4. Der sash gib dem Gnomys ruum tu settul gud!<br>
<br>
Davus.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujasiofneriak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jasi of Neriak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 5:36:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ang.mux.net/smjasi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> Keep the Haste. You can make up the AC in other items. As a melee class, the most signifigant increase to your damage is when you add Haste. You swing more often, therefore hit more often and agro more often.<br>
<br>
As a Rogue, it also allows me to BACKSTAB more often. I am not sure, but the same theory might also work on your taunt, kick, bash and other abilities.<br>
<br>
Mmmm... Haste... Casters have their crack, melee types have ours..<br>
<br>
(I wonder if Verant realized they were creating a drug dealer class when they created Enchanters?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarisscaleblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maris Scale Blade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 6:26:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Finrod?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> As an alternate there ARE a few other haste belts in the game that DO have AC on them /w Haste. Just becasue everyone and there brother uses a FBSS dosen't mean its the only thing out there. If you need to choose between the two, choose the FBSS for sure, just remeber later that there are ac/haste items as well.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrylliumcalaquendi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tryllium Calaquendi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 6:43:20 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eatel.net/~usafcajun/drunks/sigpics/sigpictryllium.gif width=80 height=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> What they all said.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uitarki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Itarki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 9:48:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> stay with the FBSS ... I would much rather have the haste than more AC. ANd the damn belt weighs too damn much. But then again I am a caster so what do I know =)<br>
<br>
  Itarki Icewynd<br>
  47 Wizard<br>
  Sentinels of Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeatrixmaledicta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beatrix Maledicta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 7:08:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> If you don't get the aggro, you don't need the AC anyway. So you're stuck with the FBSS if you have a problem with taunting - that's how I reason anyway.<br>
<br>
When I think of it I remember having a hard time with taunting during the 30s too. For some reason it got better later on. I doubt it was an equipment issue though. Rather, my guess is it has to do with three other things: <br>
i) warrior skill effectiveness at that level versus other melee classes (read: it will get better)<br>
ii) when you have a problem with taunt for some time you're bound to pick up some of the things you can do to improve your chances of getting aggro<br>
iii) other meleers (and other classes) pick up things too that help you do your job, e.g. hybrids going easy with their spells before you have secured aggro, monks adapting their equipment to suit the situation, pullers pulling with aggro range rather than offensive means, etc etc. Taunting is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> just <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> your</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> job - a warrior can only do so much.<br>
<br>
Too bad your yaks don't proc at your level because the procs are very good taunts. Otherwise your equipment should be perfectly adequate. Just avoid using high dly 2H weapons when fighting high blues and up because you will always miss blows against high cons and missed blows with low dly weapons has a more limited effect on taunting overall.<br>
<br>
All that in mind, I still wouldn't bother to switch the FBSS for the SSB occasionally. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalaena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talaena</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.dangermouse.org/images/penfold/funny3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Where's my Tang? </span><br>  Posts: 2729<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 9:40:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.dangermouse.org/images/penfold/funny3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> Thank you all for the input. One tihng that donned on me is that I always seem to be the punk-ass tank bitx in the group; that may be one reason for the lack of taunt ability. :-)<br>
<br>
When i'm 34 and the SK is 42; I am not taunting off of him very easily...<br>
<br>
Here's sorta a side thought:<br>
<br>
With my mith staff at 28/46 (I tihnk); I find myself taunting MUCH easier than with 2 non-proccing yaks, my icetooth/gleaming (11 and 10/29) or anything else I've had. <br>
<br>
The DPM on that mith staff seems to be a few degrees higher than my other weapons, even if it is a 2hb... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 860<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/30/01 11:55:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.242.60.166/chicktourney_com/larges/415.jpg width=110 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FBSS or Straw Spun Belt?</span><hr size=1> You don't offhand nearly as much as your mainhand swings.  You don't have nearly the same damage output, so the stick is better.  When your offhand is swinging a lot more (level 50+) 1h weapons are the only way to go. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
